shot\n\n4. **ProbabilityEditCommand** - Edit probability values (for CPT)\n   - Takes array of `DraftEdit` objects\n   - `execute()` → applies drafts\n   - `undo()` → reverts drafts\n\n#### **useDraftEdits.ts** (frontend/src/features/history/)\nLocal draft management for probability edits with undo/redo support.\n\n**Purpose:** Stage probability edits locally before committing to server.\n\n**API:**\n```typescript\ninterface DraftEdit {\n  entryIndex: number;\n  outcomeId: string;\n  probability: number;\n  context: Array<{ variableId: string; outcomeId: string }>;\n  previousProbability: number;\n  hadPriorDraft?: boolean;  // Was there a prior draft?\n}\n\nfunction useDraftEdits() {\n  stageDraft(edit: DraftEdit): void;           // Stage + push to history\n  getDraft(entryIndex, outcomeId): number | undefined;\n  clearDrafts(): void;                          // Discard all local drafts\n  hasDrafts: boolean;\n  allDrafts(): DraftEdit[];\n  drafts: Map<string, DraftEdit>;\n}\n```\n\n**Key pattern:**\n- Uses `draftKey = \"entryIndex::outcomeId\"` to track by cell\n- `stageDraft()` creates a `ProbabilityEditCommand` and pushes to history\n- When undoing a draft, intelligently restores previous draft value or removes entry\n- Works even without `HistoryProvider` (graceful degradation)\n\n#### **useHistoryAssumptions.ts** (frontend/src/features/history/)\nWrapper around `useAssumptions()` that adds history tracking.\n\n**Wraps methods:**\n- `addAssumption()` → creates `AssumptionAddCommand`\n- `removeAssumption()` → creates `AssumptionRemoveCommand`\n- `clearAll()` → creates `AssumptionClearAllCommand`\n\n**Pattern:** Each mutation creates command, executes it, then pushes to history.\n\n#### **useUndoRedoKeyboard.ts** (frontend/src/features/history/)\nGlobal keyboard shortcut handling.\n\n**Shortcuts:**\n- `Ctrl+Z` (or `Cmd+Z` on Mac) → undo\n- `Ctrl+Shift+Z` or `Ctrl+Y` → redo\n\n**Smart behavior:**\n- Skips when focused element is INPUT, TEXTAREA, SELECT, or contenteditable\n- Only fires if history has items (canUndo/canRedo checks)\n- Prevents browser default with `e.preventDefault()`\n\n#### **UndoRedoToolbar.tsx** (frontend/src/features/history/)\nUI component showing undo/redo buttons.\n\n**Display:**\n- Undo button (disabled if !canUndo)\n- Redo button (disabled if !canRedo)\n- Status text showing \"X undos / Y redos\"\n- Tooltips showing command descriptions\n\n#### **CptPanel.tsx** (frontend/src/features/trading/)\nConditional Probability Table editor - primary user of draft edits and history.\n\n**Integration with undo/redo:**\n- Uses `useDraftEdits()` to stage probability edits\n- `handleCellClick()` → opens editor UI\n- `handleSubmit()` → calls `stageDraft()` (creates command, pushes to history)\n- `handleCommitDrafts()` → submits all drafts to server API\n- Shows asterisk (*) on drafted cells\n- \"Discard drafts\" button clears without committing\n\n**Three-state probability values:**\n1. Server value (from API)\n2. Draft value (locally staged, with undo support)\n3. Editing value (in input slider)\n\n---\n\n### 3. EXISTING UNDO/REDO TEST SUITE\n\nLocated in: **frontend/src/__tests__/**\n\n#### **HistoryContext.test.tsx** (244 lines)\nTests the core undo/redo reducer:\n- Initial state (empty stacks)\n- Push operations (adds to undo, clears redo)\n- Undo operations (calls command.undo(), moves to redo)\n- Redo operations (calls command.execute(), moves to undo)\n- Clear operation (empties both stacks)\n- History cap enforcement (max 50 items)\n- Multiple undo/redo cycles\n- Error handling (throws when used outside provider)\n\n#### **commands.test.ts** (186 lines)\nTests all Command classes:\n- **AssumptionAddCommand**: execute/undo with/without previous\n- **AssumptionRemoveCommand**: execute/undo restoration\n- **AssumptionClearAllCommand**: snapshot correctness, mutation safety\n- **ProbabilityEditCommand**: draft application/reversion, descriptions\n\n#### **useDraftEdits.test.tsx** (139 lines)\nTests draft management:\n- Initial state (no drafts)\n- Staging drafts (makes retrievable)\n- History integration (pushes commands)\n- Undo reverts drafts properly\n- Redo re-applies drafts\n- Clear drafts\n- Multiple cell tracking\n- Works without HistoryProvider\n\n#### **useUndoRedoKeyboard.test.tsx** (147 lines)\nTests keyboard shortcuts:\n- `isEditableElement()` utility (INPUT, TEXTAREA, SELECT, contenteditable)\n- Ctrl+Z triggers undo\n- Ctrl+Shift+Z and Ctrl+Y trigger redo\n- Cmd+Z on Mac\n- Respects focused editable elements (doesn't fire in inputs)\n- Respects history state (canUndo/canRedo)\n\n#### **AssumptionContext.test.tsx** (136 lines)\nTests assumption state management (without history):\n- Initial state\n- addAssumption (single, multiple, replacement)\n- removeAssumption\n- clearAll\n- hasAssumption/getAssumption queries\n- contextPayload generation\n- Error when used outside provider\n\n---\n\n### 4. TESTING FRAMEWORK & SETUP\n\n**Framework:** Vitest (modern Jest alternative)\n**React Testing:** @testing-library/react\n**DOM Testing:** jsdom environment\n\n**Configuration files:**\n\n**vitest.config.ts:**\n```typescript\nexport default defineConfig({\n  plugins: [react()],\n  resolve: { alias: { \"@\": \"./src\" } },\n  test: {\n    environment: \"jsdom\",\n    setupFiles: [\"./src/__tests__/setup.ts\"],\n    globals: true,\n  },\n});\n```\n\n**package.json scripts:**\n```json\n\"test\": \"vitest run\",\n\"test:watch\": \"vitest\",\n\"lint\": \"eslint src/\"\n```\n\n**setup.ts:**\n```typescript\nimport \"@testing-library/jest-dom/vitest\";\n```\n\n**helpers.tsx:** Custom test utilities\n- `renderWithProviders()` - wraps components with QueryClient, SessionProvider, MemoryRouter\n- `createMockQueryResult()` - factory for mock query hooks\n- `createMockMutationResult()` - factory for mock mutation hooks\n\n**Test patterns used:**\n- `vi.fn()` for mocking functions\n- `vi.mock()` for module mocking\n- `renderHook()` from @testing-library/react for hook testing\n- `act()` for state updates\n- `renderWithProviders()` for component integration tests\n- `fireEvent()` for user interactions\n\n**tsconfig.json:**\n```typescript\n- target: ES2020\n- lib: ES2020, DOM, DOM.Iterable\n- strict mode enabled\n- path alias: \"@/*\" → \"./src/*\"\n- jsx: react-jsx (automatic JSX transform)\n```\n\n---\n\n### 5. ARCHITECTURAL PATTERNS\n\n#### Provider Hierarchy\n```\nApp.tsx\n├── Providers (QueryClientProvider, SessionProvider, RouterProvider)\n│   └── Routes\n│       └── MarketDetail (for active markets)\n│           ├── HistoryProvider (enables undo/redo)\n│           │   └── AssumptionProvider (enables assumptions)\n│           │       ├── UndoRedoToolbar\n│           │       ├── AssumptionPanel\n│           │       ├── CptPanel\n│           │       └── ... other trading panels\n│           └── (for inactive markets - no HistoryProvider)\n```\n\n#### State Management Strategy\n1. **AssumptionContext** - pure state, no side effects\n2. **HistoryContext** - command history, reducer pattern\n3. **useDraftEdits** - local drafts, integrates with history\n4. **useHistoryAssumptions** - wraps assumption mutations with history\n5. **useUndoRedoKeyboard** - side effect handler for keyboard\n\n#### Command Pattern\n- Generic `Command` interface (description, execute, undo)\n- Concrete commands for each operation type\n- Commands are immutable (close over captured state)\n- Commands stored in stacks, not replayed\n- Undo calls command.undo(), not re-executing history\n\n#### Integration Pattern\n- CptPanel uses `useDraftEdits()` to stage changes\n- Staging creates command, executes it, pushes to history\n- User can undo/redo before committing\n- On commit, all drafts sent to server API\n- Server is source of truth, local drafts are ephemeral\n\n---\n\n### 6. KEY IMPLEMENTATION DETAILS\n\n**Assumption snapshots (critical for correctness):**\n- `AssumptionClearAllCommand` copies assumption array: `[...opts.previousAssumptions]`\n- Prevents mutations to source array from affecting undo\n\n**Draft previous value tracking:**\n- Each `DraftEdit` stores `previousProbability` and `hadPriorDraft` flag\n- On undo: if `!hadPriorDraft`, removes entry; else restores value\n- Handles case where user edits same cell multiple times\n\n**History cap behavior:**\n- Max 50 commands stored: `.slice(-HISTORY_CAP)`\n- Oldest commands evicted first (FIFO depth)\n- Redo stack cleared on new command push\n\n**Keyboard shortcut safety:**\n- Checks if focused element is editable before triggering\n- Uses both Ctrl/Cmd modifiers for cross-platform support\n- Supports both Shift+Z and Y for redo on Windows\n\n---\n\n### 7. COMPONENT INTEGRATION EXAMPLES\n\n**CptPanel using draft edits:**\n```typescript\nconst draftEdits = useDraftEdits();\n\nconst handleSubmit = () => {\n  draftEdits.stageDraft({  // Creates command, pushes to history\n    entryIndex: editing.entryIndex,\n    outcomeId: editing.outcomeId,\n    probability: editing.probability,\n    context: entry.context,\n    previousProbability: currentP,\n  });\n};\n\nconst handleCommitDrafts = () => {\n  for (const draft of draftEdits.allDrafts()) {\n    mutation.mutate({ ... });  // Send to server\n  }\n  draftEdits.clearDrafts();  // Clear local drafts after commit\n};\n```\n\n**MarketDetail conditional providers:**\n```typescript\n{m.status === \"active\" ? (\n  <HistoryProvider>\n    <AssumptionProvider>\n      <UndoRedoToolbar />\n      <AssumptionPanel market={m} />\n      <CptPanel market={m} />\n      {/* ... */}\n    </AssumptionProvider>\n  </HistoryProvider>\n) : (\n  // Inactive markets: no undo/redo\n  <>\n    <CptPanel market={m} />\n    {/* ... */}\n  </>\n)}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 8. TESTING PATTERNS OBSERVED\n\n**Unit tests for hooks:**\n```typescript\nfunction wrapper({ children }: { children: ReactNode }) {\n  return <HistoryProvider>{children}</HistoryProvider>;\n}\nconst { result } = renderHook(() => useHistory(), { wrapper });\nact(() => result.current.push(cmd));\nexpect(result.current.canUndo).toBe(true);\n```\n\n**Mocking in component tests:**\n```typescript\nvi.mock(\"@/lib/query/hooks\", () => ({\n  useMarket: vi.fn(),\n  useCpt: vi.fn(),\n  // ...\n}));\nconst mockUseMarket = vi.mocked(useMarket);\nmockUseMarket.mockReturnValue(defaultQueryState(mockMarketData));\n```\n\n**Helper factory for consistent mocks:**\n```typescript\nfunction defaultQueryState<T>(data?: T) {\n  return {\n    data,\n    isLoading: false,\n    error: null,\n    isFetching: false,\n    // ... 15+ more properties\n  };\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 9. SUMMARY: READY FOR IMPLEMENTATION\n\nThe codebase has:\n\n✓ Complete undo/redo infrastructure (History + Command pattern)\n✓ Existing tests for all core features (6,000+ lines of test code)\n✓ Draft system for local edits before commit\n✓ Keyboard shortcut integration\n✓ Context-based provider pattern\n✓ Type-safe with strict TypeScript\n✓ Separation of concerns (contexts, hooks, components)\n✓ Graceful degradation (works without HistoryProvider)\n✓ Test helpers and mocking utilities\n✓ Clear patterns for extending (add new Command subclasses)\n\nFor implementing new undo/redo features, you would:\n1. Create new `Command` subclass in `commands.ts`\n2. Wrap relevant hook with history tracking (similar to `useHistoryAssumptions`)\n3. Use `history.push(cmd)` after executing commands\n4. Write tests following existing patterns\n5. Integrate UI (buttons, tooltips, etc.)\n\nAll tests use **Vitest** with **@testing-library/react**, running in **jsdom**, with **React Query** mocking patterns."}],"totalDurationMs":75533,"totalTokens":59920,"totalToolUseCount":33,"usage":{"input_tokens":5,"cache_creation_input_tokens":461,"cache_read_input_tokens":54426,"output_tokens":5028,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":461},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
